              "choices": [
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_1",
                  "content": "He calculated that the population would increase in an arithmetic progression, while food production would increase in a slower geometric progression. This would mean that there would soon be too much food."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_2",
                  "content": "He calculated that scientific advancements would increase in a geometric progression, which would greatly reduce infant mortality rates and increase life expectancies."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_3",
                  "content": "He calculated that scientific advancements would increase in an arithmetic progression, which would greatly reduce infant mortality rates and increase life expectancies."
                },
